So I am using the image gallery module (which is using slick slider) and I am trying to run the `init` property on slick, problem is the following doesnt work:
```
$('.slick-slider').on('init', function(event, slick){
    console.log("initialized")
});
```
is there something else that the `init` should be on?

Also for those wondering, you can fire events when an image is loaded as well using:
```
$('.slick-slide img').on('load', function(event, slick){
      [Run Some code here]
    });
```
`note: it will run EVERY time an image is loaded, so may not be ideal`
